                            <h2 class="section-heading"> Steps to get Certification of Capability in Business Analysis </h2>
                            <p style="display:inline;">CCBA® stands for Certification of Competency in Business Analysis. It is the gold standard that validates your experience and skill in Business Analysis. The CCBA Certification training at KnowledgeHut prepares you to clear your CCBA exam and obtain the certification. </p>
                            <p style="display:inline;">This training also provides you with the mandatory 21 hours of Professional Development that are necessary to take the CCBA exam. If you want to earn a CCBA certification, you can follow these steps:</p><span class="view-more-link">.....</span> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="view-more-link">View more</a>
                            <div class="view-more-data editor-content" id="path-to-cert-data" style="display:none;">
                                <p>This training also provides you with the mandatory 21 hours of Professional Development that are necessary to take the CCBA exam. If you want to earn a CCBA certification, you can follow these steps:<br></p>
                                <p><b>1. Get Trained&nbsp;</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li></li>
                                    <li>Enrol in a focused CCBA course from a reputed, IIBA® Endorsed Education Provider (EEP™) like KnowledgeHut and complete the training. Earn the required 21 Professional Development contact hours needed to appear for the CCBA® exam.&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Ensure that you meet the criteria of having 3750 hours of Business Analysis work experience in 7 years, of which 900 hours must be completed in each of 2 of the 6 BABOK® Guide Knowledge Areas OR, a minimum of 500 hours must be completed in each of 4 of the 6 BABOK® Guide Knowledge Areas.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>2. Take the CCBA® Exam&nbsp;</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The CCBA exam is an online, proctored exam, that you can take online, or at a PSI test center. Register with IIBA to schedule the exam.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Answer all the 130 multiple choice questions within the allotted 3 hours. You will be notified at the end of the exam whether you managed to pass.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>3. Flaunt your Badge!&nbsp;</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Congratulations! You have cleared the CCBA exam and received the CCBA Badge. Make sure to add it to your professional profiles and forge your successful Business Analyst career.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
